ar to the post-Fordist, neo-Liberal state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aCoursebook. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aDeniger, Marc-Andre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHardina, Donna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLightman, Ernie S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMullaly, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurphy, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShragge, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShragge, Eric, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSwanson, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144260311040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442603110423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442603110.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK